  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to examine the efficacy of mid-infrared spectroscopy together
      with Attenuated Total Reflection (ATR), for the detection of gynecological malignancies in
      real time during surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
